adrian daub republics of letters a journal for the study of knowledge politics and the arts link to arcade home editors blog issues rss contact admin login home adrian daub adrian daub email website is assistant professor of german studies at stanford university where he specializes in nineteenth century aesthetics politics and culture he is the author of a german language book on the culture of four hand piano playing in the nineteenth century and the author of uncivil unions the metaphysics of marriage in early german idealism and jena romanticism forthcoming from university of chicago press he is an editor of republics of letters fora between experience and experiment limits of the atlantic republican tradition on sovereignty rethinking the republic of letters the leland stanford jr university seal issn 2159 1873
